[6], exposure  problems exist when buyers desire a bundle of goods but may only participate in single-item auctions.1 For example, if Alice values a video game console by itself for $200, a video game by itself for $30, and both a console and game for $250, Alice must determine how much of the $20 of synergy value she might include in her bid for the console alone.
We believe that one leading place of resistance is in the lack of provably optimal bidding  strategies for any but the simplest of market designs.
